<br>
The postion of the GMs and what they will enforce is this<br>
<br>
1. They do not recognize camps or claims of camps. If 2 groups want to kill mobs at the same location then they need to share. <br>
<br>
2. Whoever first aggros a mob has the right to kill it and get the reward.<br>
<br>
3. You should not pull or aggro mobs in such away that they attack other groups.<br>
<br>
    Virtually all the other rules we all play by are informal aggrements and rules of conduct most players have come to accept, an expect acceptance by other players.<br>
       I think we all have a rough idea of what those informal agreements and expectations are but there are a number of situations which are borderline or ambiguous.<br>
<br>
   I am not aware of any generally accepted agreement, to when multiple camps can be claimed.  For example in Velks if a group was to set up by the zone and claim Back Wall, Left wall, right wall and fake wall, I seriously doubt weather any one would respect their claim, even if they could kill all those mobs before they respawn. On the other hand the &quot;top&quot; group routinely claims almost as many spawns and they regularly become irate if any one challenges them.<br>
<br>
    In  the case of Seb and AOE groups. It seems to me that if an AOE group claims most all the zone, and you would are the member of a regular group, the advice given to ask the AOE group if you could have a particular camp is correct.  If the AOE group refuses then it makes sence to either leave or move your group to the location you want  to camp. If there is no one at that spot then you should notify the AOE group where you are located and ask them not to &quot;train&quot; you or overwhelm your group with aggroed mobs. I would snapshot(the thing you do so you can save text and send to GMs) your request and their reply.  <br>
   It is my guess the GM would back you up on two counts. One the general requirement to share and the requirement to not knowingly aggro mobs which will attack another group.<br>
<br>
   <br>
   <br>
<br>
