<br>
KS and kiting<br>
With only a few exceptions (dragons are a very good example) first to engage a mob, does damage, and has suffient force to kill it gets the kill. That means if you snare a wyvern (without hurting the mob) and someone else hits it technically they are an ass but they are not ks-ing you.  Sort of like that Slvyester Stalone movie, its all about First Blood. <br>
<br>
Bigger mobs<br>
If you kite (say Lozidal) to buy time for your guild/friends to arrive the mob the mob isn't yours either as you have insufficient force to kill him.  VI doesn't respect silly people using delaying tactics to prevent punctual parties from killing spawns you decide to run all over a zone.   <br>
<br>
Camps<br>
VI does not recognize camping (per se).  Yes that means stupid people that petition their camp was &quot;ganked&quot; will typically find little help from VI.  <br>
<br>
Yes, on a case by case basis, some guides or GMs will assist someone on a quest to ensure that another person(s) does not &quot;intentionally&quot; interfere.  Try killing dorfs during a ring war in GD (if the host of the event doesn't say its ok) and see how fast you get a warning &quot;if&quot; they catch you doing it. <br>
<br>
Most guides/GMs try to stay out of it and leave it to us to work it out.  Quite frankly, once you leave orc camp1 unless you are a raid size force gm's really don't want to deal with petty squabbles and typical suggest you try to work something out or move on.  Guides tend to be more apt to try to make you share mobs but I have seen people go to chat find a real gm and have the guide reprimanded for over stepping or abusing their authority.  You don't see the reprimand but you do get a nice tell from a GM to continue on and the guide goes away.  I respect guides trying to help out but many need a lot of time before they truly grasp their limited power and bounds. <br>
<br>
So you are mad so don't get angry get even...<br>
People tend to get mad, ks or intentional train others, and that (on the other hand) will get a gm involved.  IMO, if you are not stupid you don't tell anyone ever that you are petitioning them.  If you are mad enough to petition why blow a great chance to see them go up in flames?<br>
<br>
People who blatantly ks and train to get rid of you are very easy to deal with.  My favorite is &quot;if you don't do _insert demand, I will train you&quot;.  <br>
<br>
Let me think what to do...oh yah  /report offending line and person name then do a petition asking a gm to observe invis.<br>
<br>
About 50 percent of the time a gm will come in invis to watch your incredible stupidity and amazingly that character goes poof about 50 percent of the time and maybe 10 percent of the time is never see again. <br>
<br>
MT is a play nice server where we are suppose to try to make it a friendly place (with at least some sense of civility) most of the time.  <br>
<br>
VI does not require the respect of camps, nor in most cases to they recognize them (you do seem to get help in disputed epic camps).<br>
<br>
So if the question is can you take a camp if someone is claiming more than one and get away with it...actually the answer is yes. Should you is a totally diferent issue.  Just remember the more people you fight with means the more enemies you have to deal with later on.  <br>
<br>
I have had my share of being an ass in game and have tempered my attitude considerably but just remember the less people you tick off the more likely you get that free rez, port, buff, or one day uber guild invite because you didn't make it to yet another person's (beside the computer) fu forever list. <br>
<br>
Just a thought<br>
<br>
